00:32.115 --> 00:33.491
He's a two time All-Star.

00:33.575 --> 00:34.743
Yeah, just like you.

00:34.826 --> 00:36.536
Yeah, but that ain't right.

00:37.078 --> 00:40.040
Probably got tired.
Wanted to trade, you know what I mean?

00:40.498 --> 00:42.208
He'll get picked up, quick too.

00:42.292 --> 00:43.668
Won't play for the Yankees, though.
Still root for him, though.

00:45.754 --> 00:47.714
Nah, if he ain't a Yankee,
nothing to root for.

00:48.339 --> 00:49.424
You cold, Tron.

00:49.799 --> 00:51.051
What? I'm just saying.

00:51.134 --> 00:52.886
No french fries for traitors, man.

00:52.969 --> 00:55.555
Whoa, I ain't no traitor.
I am loyal to the soil.

00:55.638 --> 00:57.849
-You know what I'm saying?
-A'ight, we gonna see.

00:59.225 --> 01:02.979
'Cause, you know, usually I just let
everybody else go and take the lead,

01:03.063 --> 01:04.773
but today, I was like, "I wanna step up.

01:04.856 --> 01:06.649
I'm gonna do what I have to do,"
and I did.

01:06.733 --> 01:08.693
And I really feel like
if I keep doing that,

01:08.777 --> 01:10.945
then I could really take first chair.
I really do.

01:11.029 --> 01:13.615
-[boy laughs]
-And you sounded good today, too.

01:14.741 --> 01:17.035
All right,
you got your music lesson out the way.

01:17.243 --> 01:18.328
You're a free man.

01:18.703 --> 01:20.455
Don't waste this spring break, Kev.

01:21.164 --> 01:22.749
Spring break's for relaxing, Angie.

01:22.832 --> 01:25.210
How about you relax your way
into those dishes from last night

01:25.293 --> 01:26.586
-before Mama gets home?
-Okay.

01:26.669 --> 01:28.338
I'm closing at work tonight.
Don't wait up.

01:28.421 --> 01:29.297
All right.

01:30.298 --> 01:33.718
Come on, baby girl,
let's go get some chicken at Kennedy.

01:33.802 --> 01:36.721
-How come you always hungry?
-How come you <i>never </i>hungry?

01:37.013 --> 01:38.306
'Cause I eat at lunch.

01:38.389 --> 01:39.390
At school.

01:39.557 --> 01:40.517
That's why.

01:40.600 --> 01:41.518
Mm!

01:41.601 --> 01:42.602
Look at me.

01:42.894 --> 01:45.396
And if you would come to school
more often,

01:45.730 --> 01:48.274
then we could spend more time together.

01:51.152 --> 01:54.906
Well, I was waiting for you to get out
of school so we could eat together.

01:54.989 --> 01:56.449
Everything better with you.

01:58.493 --> 02:01.204
Come on, let's get us some Kennedy.
Please, baby. Yeah?

02:02.163 --> 02:03.581
Yo, ease up.

02:03.665 --> 02:06.584
Don't let's get there first.
Make Sharene go inside, and...

02:06.793 --> 02:08.795
-you know, be looking around for me.
-Oh, boy.

02:08.878 --> 02:10.964
She is not checking for...
What are you doing?

02:11.047 --> 02:13.758
