[excited chatter and laughter]

05:45.845 --> 05:47.555
[man] Ah, what have we got here?

05:47.638 --> 05:50.183
[ominous music playing]

05:54.520 --> 05:55.688
[man 1] What you gonna do?

05:55.772 --> 05:58.232
[man 2] Bunch of white dudes jumped me
in the Bronx last week.

05:58.316 --> 05:59.942
[man 1] Man, stop playing yourself!

06:00.026 --> 06:01.361
[attackers laughing]

06:01.486 --> 06:02.862
[victim groans]

06:04.238 --> 06:05.239
[man 3] Get up!

06:05.782 --> 06:07.742
-[man 2] Payback's a bitch.
-Go!

06:07.825 --> 06:09.202
[siren wailing]

06:09.285 --> 06:11.704
[woman] <i>Police operator 414,</i>
<i>which emergency?</i>

06:11.788 --> 06:14.624
-[man] Police! Run!
-[man 1] <i>...about 30 or 40 male blacks</i>

06:14.707 --> 06:16.084
-Come on!
-[man 1] <i>...inside Central Park,</i>

06:16.167 --> 06:18.544
<i>approximately at 100th Street</i>
<i>and East Drive.</i>

06:18.628 --> 06:22.298
[man 2] <i>...by a group of</i>
<i>seven male Hispanic youths.</i>

06:22.382 --> 06:24.342
-[approaching sirens]
-[man 2] <i>It's a roving band.</i>

06:24.425 --> 06:26.969
[man 3]
<i>...four or five male black teenagers</i>

06:27.053 --> 06:29.639
<i>and possibly used some sort of weapon,</i>

06:29.722 --> 06:31.265
<i>a bat or a stick of some sort.</i>

06:32.725 --> 06:35.686
[man 4] <i>Be advised, Central. The group</i>
<i>is heading towards 107th Street.</i>

06:35.770 --> 06:36.729
[man] Get up! Get up!

06:36.813 --> 06:39.232
[man 5] <i>Central, the last assault,</i>
<i>where did that take place?</i>

06:39.315 --> 06:41.859
[woman] <i>That was at nine-six</i>
<i>and the West Drive.</i>

06:42.110 --> 06:44.570
-[man 6] <i>Now heading north.</i>
-[woman] <i>Heading north?</i>

06:44.654 --> 06:45.780
[man 6] <i>Coming right to us.</i>

06:45.863 --> 06:47.156
[panting]

06:47.240 --> 06:49.242
[tires screech]

06:49.951 --> 06:51.577
-Police!
-[man] It's the cops!

06:51.661 --> 06:54.414
-[suspenseful music playing]
-[officer 1] Stop there!

06:55.748 --> 06:57.875
-[officer 1] Get down!
-[officer 2] Stop!

06:58.376 --> 06:59.335
[grunts]

07:01.087 --> 07:03.172
[indistinct shouting]

07:04.090 --> 07:06.884
[officer] Stop now!
Stop right now! Right fucking now!

07:07.802 --> 07:09.804
[siren wailing]

07:10.221 --> 07:11.097
[man] Go!

07:13.641 --> 07:15.059
[men struggling]

07:15.643 --> 07:19.188
-[officer] Little animal, stop!
-Stop it! I didn't do nothing!

07:19.397 --> 07:21.774
-I swear I didn't do--
-[officer] Don't run!

07:29.157 --> 07:31.659
[insects chirping]

07:41.461 --> 07:43.546
[man on police radio]
<i>Dispatch, 14-Charlie-7.</i>

07:43.838 --> 07:46.924
<i>We got a 10-92 on West 42nd Street</i>

07:47.008 --> 07:48.301
<i>just east of Broadway.</i>

07:48.676 --> 07:50.094
<i>White male...</i>

07:50.678 --> 07:51.512
[man] Morning.

07:51.888 --> 07:53.473
-It's bad?
-Yeah.

07:53.931 --> 07:57.226
White female adult with severe injuries
to the face and body.

07:57.310 --> 07:58.269
[Fairstein] Uh-huh.

07:58.478 --> 07:59.979
[man] Yeah, watch your step.

08:00.062 --> 08:02.315
-[Fairstein] Any press here yet?
-[man] Not yet.

08:09.614 --> 08:10.573
[Fairstein sighs]

08:12.283 --> 08:14.160
-Still alive?
-Yeah.

08:20.958 --> 08:23.503
What the fuck was she doing here?

08:25.796 --> 08:26.756
Uh...

08:26.839 --> 08:28.049
Time of discovery?

08:29.258 --> 08:33.262
1:30 a.m. Couple of beaners were out
for a midnight stroll, called it in.

08:33.930 --> 08:37.975
[Fairstein] Could... Ah-ah! Could you...
Let's make sure to get these drag marks.

08:38.184 --> 08:39.185
He dragged her in.

08:39.894 --> 08:42.271
Just like... right there.

08:42.480 --> 08:43.814
Look, clear as day.

08:44.732 --> 08:45.775
His footsteps.

08:47.068 --> 08:47.944
Her body.

08:49.195 --> 08:50.238
Fucking hell.

09:03.876 --> 09:06.921
I gotta get this statement out.
There are a few reporters out there.

09:07.296 --> 09:12.552
The assault on the female jogger occurred
in the North Park at approximately, um...

09:13.344 --> 09:16.347
let's say between 10:00 to 11:00 p.m.

09:17.056 --> 09:20.309
The jogger is believed to have been
running on...

09:20.810 --> 09:24.230
the East Drive when she was struck
on the back of the head,

09:24.313 --> 09:27.024
dragged into the brush, severely beaten,
and raped.

09:27.108 --> 09:28.609
Sheehan, who's here?

09:29.068 --> 09:33.155
Did you pick up any gays or homeless
or anything?

09:33.239 --> 09:35.199
You know, maybe somebody saw something.

09:35.283 --> 09:38.286
Rosario said it got pretty lively
up there.

09:38.369 --> 09:40.454
-Oh, yeah?
-His unit collared a bunch of turds

09:40.538 --> 09:42.832
up at the north end of the park,
goofing off.

09:43.666 --> 09:45.293
Okay, what is this?

09:45.459 --> 09:46.335
"Willing"?

09:47.420 --> 09:48.254
"Wheeling--"
What is that?

09:49.839 --> 09:52.341
[female officer] Uh, it says "wiling out"?

09:54.760 --> 09:55.803
What's "wilding"?

09:58.806 --> 10:00.766
-I'm here for my son.
-[officer] Okay.

10:01.309 --> 10:02.560
Kevin Richardson?

10:02.935 --> 10:05.396
He's 14, in the eighth grade.

10:05.479 --> 10:07.398
[officer] Reynolds, Santanas.

10:08.316 --> 10:09.525
[Reynolds] Mr. Santana.

10:09.734 --> 10:11.277
-[officer] Next.
-Took you long enough.

10:11.444 --> 10:13.613
We call you at 5:00 a.m.
and you show up at 8:00?

10:13.696 --> 10:17.116
I'm sorry. I gotta work. I was sleeping--

10:17.199 --> 10:19.619
[Reynolds] Sleep well with your kid
running loose in the park?

10:19.702 --> 10:22.163
No, my son never gave me no problems.

10:22.246 --> 10:24.582
Except when he breaks the law?
Give me that one on top.

10:24.665 --> 10:26.751
-Come on, sir. What--
-[Reynolds] Bring this to family court.

10:26.834 --> 10:28.753
What's the law that he broke? Come on.

10:28.836 --> 10:30.046
Unlawful assembly.

10:30.171 --> 10:31.797
Next shift will process him out.

10:31.881 --> 10:34.634
Wait, next shift? But I gotta get to work.

10:34.717 --> 10:35.843
I gotta work.

10:36.260 --> 10:37.720
Sir, I gotta--

10:37.803 --> 10:40.306
-Detective Farrell.
-Interview room with the kids.

10:40.389 --> 10:42.350
-[woman in Spanish] Ray can't leave?
-[Santana in English] I gotta go, man.

10:42.433 --> 10:45.394
-I gotta go, I'm really late.
-[officer] I understand. If he's under 16,

10:45.478 --> 10:48.481
-legally your son has to have an adult--
-[Santana] I know, but you know what?

10:48.564 --> 10:52.234
I'm already late for work, okay?
I don't know what else to do.

10:52.443 --> 10:54.570
My mother's here. Maybe she can stay.

10:54.654 --> 10:57.657
But, <i>mira,</i> the thing is that
she don't even got no English.

10:57.740 --> 11:01.327
-[officer] We have translators here...
-[Santana] I'll be fired if I don't go.

11:03.913 --> 11:05.122
What happened to that one?

11:05.498 --> 11:07.833
Bunch of wise-asses
out in the park last night.

11:08.167 --> 11:10.419
Hassling bicyclists, beating up people.

11:10.503 --> 11:13.214
They're only 13, 14 at most.

11:13.297 --> 11:15.633
Parents are coming in
for family court tickets.

11:16.133 --> 11:17.301
What's "wilding"?

11:18.386 --> 11:20.346
-What's that?
-You said on your report here

11:20.429 --> 11:22.598
they were "wilding." What's that mean?

11:23.891 --> 11:25.643
[Farrell] I don't know.
One of them said it.

11:34.568 --> 11:35.444
Hey.

11:37.571 --> 11:39.699
What were you doing in the park
last night?

11:41.283 --> 11:43.285
Uh, nothing. I wasn't doing anything--

11:43.369 --> 11:45.329
[Fairstein] Did you see some bad guys
out there

11:45.413 --> 11:47.123
-doing some bad things?
-[knocks on desk]

11:51.585 --> 11:52.545
Um...

11:53.254 --> 11:54.255
Who were you...

11:54.714 --> 11:56.424
Who were you out in the park with?

11:57.425 --> 11:59.719
-Uh, I was out with my boy Tron.
-Mm-hm.

12:00.136 --> 12:01.011
Yeah.

12:01.137 --> 12:03.806
Out "wilding" with Tron, huh?

12:06.058 --> 12:06.892
No?

12:09.979 --> 12:11.105
Is Tron here?

12:12.940 --> 12:13.941
No? Okay.

12:14.608 --> 12:16.277
What's Tron's name and address?

12:17.445 --> 12:18.320
It's okay.

12:19.613 --> 12:20.531
Um...
Antron McCray.

12:23.325 --> 12:25.327
-[Fairstein] Uh-huh.
-He live around Schomburg.

12:25.411 --> 12:27.037
I don't know an exact...

12:27.538 --> 12:29.039
-an exact address.
-It's cool.

12:30.166 --> 12:31.792
That's cool. Thank you.

12:42.094 --> 12:44.513
So you were just gonna let
possible witnesses to a rape

12:44.597 --> 12:46.307
go on a family court ticket?

12:46.474 --> 12:49.185
Wake these kids up
and start getting some information.

12:49.268 --> 12:51.937
We've got a lady raped
and clinging to life here.

12:52.229 --> 12:54.356
I want their interviews
on my desk immediately

12:54.440 --> 12:56.108
so I can put together a timeline.

12:56.567 --> 12:57.485
Let's work.

13:01.280 --> 13:02.114
Wake up.

13:04.074 --> 13:05.534
[alarm buzzing]

13:05.618 --> 13:07.411
[man on radio]
<i>Good morning, New York City!</i>

13:07.495 --> 13:10.581
[woman] <i>Z100 New York bringing you</i>
<i>the latest hits on your way to work.</i>

13:10.664 --> 13:12.750
[man] <i>At the top of the 8:00 a.m. hour.</i>

13:13.250 --> 13:14.251
[woman] <i>Early...</i>

13:34.438 --> 13:35.397
What's this, babe?

13:36.273 --> 13:37.483
[sighs]

13:37.983 --> 13:41.237
Tronny was playing in the park and fell.

13:41.904 --> 13:43.906
It was so late, I had him put 'em there.

13:48.494 --> 13:49.537
What you mean, late?

13:51.956 --> 13:54.124
Your son didn't get in till almost 10:00.

13:55.334 --> 13:57.795
Said him and Clarence got caught up
in the park...

13:59.255 --> 14:01.590
<i>Clarence got taken down</i>
<i>to the police station.</i>

14:02.800 --> 14:05.052
[man] <i>Wait, what? What happened?</i>

14:07.638 --> 14:10.641
[woman] <i>Tronny said he was</i>
<i>playing tag in the park and fell at first.</i>

14:10.724 --> 14:12.768
I was following these big kids
in the park and...

14:12.852 --> 14:13.686
Mm-hm.

14:13.769 --> 14:15.563
-[woman] <i>When he said...</i>
-It was fun at first,

14:15.646 --> 14:18.607
but then they started throwing stuff.
That wasn't cool, you know?

14:18.691 --> 14:20.776
[woman] <i>...he said some kids were</i>
<i>causing a ruckus in the park</i>

14:20.860 --> 14:22.403
<i>-and that's when he left.</i>
-We left.

14:22.486 --> 14:23.612
You left, huh?

14:23.779 --> 14:25.614
How you get mud on your pants, bro?

14:25.823 --> 14:27.032
I-I was running.

14:27.783 --> 14:28.617
From who?

14:30.077 --> 14:31.078
Th-the police.

14:34.456 --> 14:37.918
Wait. Are you trying to tell me
all y'all was running from the police?

14:38.794 --> 14:41.380
Come on, Tron, we talked about this, man!

14:41.672 --> 14:43.966
You know better than that!
I taught you better than that.

14:44.049 --> 14:45.509
[buzzing]

14:48.387 --> 14:51.557
[indistinct police radio chatter]

14:55.352 --> 14:56.854
Go on, get your jacket, okay?

14:58.522 --> 14:59.899
-Go.
-Okay.

15:10.367 --> 15:12.286
And how long we gonna be downtown for?

15:13.162 --> 15:14.038
Not long.

15:14.955 --> 15:16.123
You'll make your shift.

15:24.048 --> 15:25.382
Those the clothes from last night?

15:27.176 --> 15:28.010
No, sir.

